or 10 years If you plan to study abroad  apply as soon as possible  You must apply in person if you are applying for your first U S  passport  For more information  click here  For passport renewal information  click here  Visa requirements vary from country to country  For detailed visa requirements  visit the State Department website and select the country you ll be visiting  Then look under entry exit requirements You can also check the website for that country s embassy in the U S  for more details and updated information  If the State Department website does not have a link to the embassy  you can find links on Embassy org  You must have a passport before applying for a visa  For international cadets desiring to study at VMI click here for U S  visa information  Most countries do not require visas for summer abroad students  Check with your host country s consulate to make sure  Important visa information for study in Spain Important visa information for study in France VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 